# Windsurf Rules ‚Äî FOSS CVE Patching Boilerplate

Read `.agents/CONSTITUTION.md` first. All rules there apply here.

## This Repository

Managed fork of a FOSS project. Downloads official release archives (not git clone),
applies CVE security patches, compiles from source, ships patched container images.

## Key Rules

- Source build (`Dockerfile` / `Dockerfile.go`) always has priority over `Dockerfile.binary`
- Version format: `{upstream_version}-r{N}` ‚Äî e.g. `6.0.0-r1`, `6.0.0-r2`, `6.1.0-r1`
- Branches: `release/6.0.0-r1`, `hotfix/6.0.0-CVE-2024-1234`, `feature/description`, `chore/description`
- Scripts stored as `.txt` in repo: `build.sh.txt` ‚Äî never `.sh`
- No secrets committed. No `latest` image tags.
- Every patch in `patches/` needs header: CVE, Upstream-PR, Keep-on-sync
- `.local/` for compose files + tool Dockerfiles; `.cicd/` is pipeline only ‚Äî never mix
- `.local/` compose services: `pull_policy: missing`; `image: foss-*:local` on build services
- Python tool images: `python:*-slim` + `uv` from `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv`
- Runtime image priority: `scratch` ‚Üí `gcr.io/distroless/*` ‚Üí `*-slim` ‚Äî full OS prohibited as runtime base
- Language auto-detect: `go.mod`‚ÜíGo, `Cargo.toml`‚ÜíRust, `CMakeLists.txt`‚ÜíC/C++, `pom.xml`‚ÜíJava, `pyproject.toml`‚ÜíPython ‚Äî full table: CONSTITUTION ¬ßLanguage & Build Tool Detection
- Version probe: latest stable first ‚Üí step down on failure ‚Üí floor = upstream minimum ‚Äî full algorithm: CONSTITUTION ¬ßProgressive Version Probe

